President Biden is set to welcome Israeli President Isaac Herzog to the White House on July 18. The visit is significant as Israel celebrates its 75th anniversary and aims to emphasize the enduring partnership and friendship between the two countries. During the meeting, President Biden will reiterate the United States' unwavering commitment to Israel's security. The leaders will also explore opportunities to strengthen Israel's integration in the region and work towards a more peaceful and prosperous Middle East. President Biden will highlight the importance of shared democratic values and discuss ways to promote freedom, prosperity, and security for both Palestinians and Israelis. Additionally, they will discuss Russia's increasing military ties with Iran and Iran's destabilizing actions in the region. Vice President Harris will meet with President Herzog on July 19, and President Herzog will also have meetings with various officials and deliver a Joint Address to Congress during his visit to Washington on July 18-19.